Description: Typical range for industrial 1064 nm fiber lasers cleaning copper; start at 200 W to balance efficiency and avoid thermal damage due to copper's high reflectivity and conductivity. Max safe before substrate melting ~500 W with proper scanning. Source: IPG Photonics specs and study in Journal of Laser Applications (2018).
Near-IR wavelength optimized for Copper absorption and minimal substrate damage
Optimal spot diameter for balancing cleaning efficiency and processing speed
High repetition rate for efficient cleaning coverage while maintaining process control
Nanosecond pulse duration for effective oxide removal without excessive thermal diffusion
Optimal scanning speed for uniform cleaning with adequate energy deposition
Recommended number of passes for complete contaminant removal
Optimal pulse overlap for uniform cleaning without excessive heat accumulation
